      "writtenOn": "2016-10-21T20:47:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Yeah, and just generally to get some test coverage since that\u0027s the path Chrome will be using.\n\nWell, I’d still like for Chrome to use the new synchronization function at some point during non-early startup, and to CHECK on the result, feed it to UMA as a Crashpad registration failure, or whatever else is appropriate. But yeah, we’ll definitely want to be able to collect crashes before any synchronization is possible, so we do need to anticipate that crashes may occur before the new method is called.",
